wiki.summary: "Graveyard" is a song by American singer Halsey. It was released on September 13, 2019 through Capitol Records as the second single from her third studio album "Manic". It reached the Top 40 in fifteen countries worldwide and is certified Gold or higher in the United States, Canada, and Australia. Leading up to the track’s release, Halsey live-streamed herself painting the cover art for Manic, which was made available for pre-order in conjunction with the release of “Graveyard.” Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Graveyard" is a song by American singer Halsey. It was released on September 13, 2019 through Capitol Records as the second single from her third studio album "Manic". It reached the Top 40 in fifteen countries worldwide and is certified Gold or higher in the United States, Canada, and Australia. Leading up to the track’s release, Halsey live-streamed herself painting the cover art for Manic, which was made available for pre-order in conjunction with the release of “Graveyard.” On September 27, 2019, a vertical video for “Graveyard” was made available to Spotify. Almost a month after the song’s release, Halsey posted a music video for “Graveyard,” featuring Euphoria actress Sydney Sweeney. Read more on Last.fm.
